    "extras": [
      "March to May and September to November are the sweet spots; the Sahara feels dramatically harsher once the midsummer heat settles in.",
      "Casbah of Algiers and many M'zab public lanes can be explored for free, but palace-house visits, local-association access, or guided ksar entry often add a symbolic 200–500 DZD.",
      "Djémila and Timgad ticket booths still work best with cash in DZD, and the quoted site fees you see online usually exclude any private transport or guide.",
      "For Tassili n'Ajjer, the permit is only one part of the spend: most travelers book a bundled 4x4, guide, and camp package from Djanet.",
      "Use SNTF for comfortable north-coast rail legs, Air Algérie to save time on the huge southbound jumps, and intercity buses where rail or flights do not line up well."
    ],
